===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}

{{Han compound|螾|t1=earthworm|日|t2=sun/day|ls=psc}}.

The pictographic protoform of {{zh-l|*螾}} was borrowed to represent "period of days" in oracle bone script. In bronze inscriptions, the semantic component {{zh-l|*日|sun/day}} was added to this character. The phonetic component was mixed with another common semantic component {{zh-l|*勹|bow down}} in Warring States period, hence the incorrect analysis in ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'' of this character as {{Han compound|勹|日}}.

